    dc:creator "Whitworth, Terry" ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "A revision of the Neotropical species of Lucilia Robineau-Desvoidy (Diptera: Calliphoridae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918532>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918534>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918546>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918590>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918600>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918604>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918612>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918554>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918578>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918616>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918725>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918727> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918532>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–6. 1–2. Left lateral view of gena=g and postgena=pg showing color of setae on gena. 1. L. cluvia, setae pale. 2. L. eximia, setae dark. Left lateral view of head showing condition of setae below and behind postocular row on occiput (white arrow). 3. L. albofusca female, setae pale and weak. 4. L. ochricornis female, setae stout and dark. Left lateral view of eye facet size, see white arrows 5. L. ochricornis male, anterior and posterior facets very small. 6. L. purpurascens male, anterior facets twice the diameter of posterior facets." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4918532/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918534>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7–15. 7–9. Upper and lower calypter color. 7. L. eximia female, both pale. 8. L. japuhybensis female both dark, both sexes. 9. L. albofusca female, upper pale, lower dark, both sexes.10–11. Basicosta color left lateral view. 10. L. cluvia female, basicosta orange. 11. L. eximia female, basicosta brown. 12–15. Pattern of microtomentum on thorax viewed from the rear. 12. L. purpurascens female, heavy on whole dorsum of thorax. 13. L. woodi female, broad band on presutural area of thorax. 14. L. rognesi female, patches on presutural area of thorax. 15. L. nitida female, microtomentum absent, presutural area of thorax all polished." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4918534/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918546>
    dc:description "FIGURES 28–34. 28. L. albofusca holotype male. 29. L. nitida holotype male. 30. L. pulverulenta holotype male. 31. L. rognesi holotype male. 32. L. vulgata holotype male. 33. L. woodi holotype male. 34. Holotype labels for the above species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4918546/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918590>
    dc:description "FIGURES 87–98. Hypandrium, pre- and postgonites, and ejaculatory sclerite of male Lucilia. 87–89. L. albofusca. 90–92. L. eximia. 93–95. L. ibis. 96–98. L. japuhybensis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4918590/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918600>
    dc:description "FIGURES 123–134. Male Lucilia abdominal sternites ST1–5. 123. L. albofusca. 124. L. eximia. 125. L. ibis. 126. L. japuhybensis. 127. L. mexicana 128. L. nitida (ST1 is missing).129. L. ochricornis. 130. L. pulverulenta. 131. L. purpurascens. 132. L. rognesi. 133. L. vulgata. 134. L. woodi." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4918600/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918604>
    dc:description "FIGURES 135–138. Ovipositors of Lucilia. 135. L. albofusca. 136. L. eximia. 137. L. ibis. 138. L. japuhybensis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4918604/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918612>
    dc:description "FIGURES 147–158. Spermathecae of Lucilia. 147. L. albofusca. 148. L. eximia. 149. L. ibis. 150. L. japuhybensis. 151. L mexicana. 152. L. nitida. 153. L. ochricornis. 154. L. pulverulenta. 155. L. purpurascens. 156. L. rognesi. 157. L. vulgata. 158. L. woodi." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4918612/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918554>
    dc:description "FIGURES 39–42. Left lateral and posterior views of male genitalia of Lucilia spp. 39, 40. L. albofusca. 41, 42. L. eximia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4918554/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918578>
    dc:description "FIGURES 63–72. Phallus of male Lucilia in left lateral and dorsal views. 63, 64. L. albofusca. 65, 66. L. eximia. 67, 68. L. ibis. 69, 70. L. japuhybensis. 71, 72. L. mexicana." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4918578/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918616>
    dc:description "FIGURE 159. Map of Lucilia species found in Central America." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4918616/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918725>
    dc:description "FIGURE 160. Map of Lucilia species found in South America." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4918725/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4918727>
    dc:description "FIGURE 161. A neighbor joining tree of specimens and species of Neotropical Lucilia using CO1 DNA barcode, made with K2P distance and generated in BOLD." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4918727/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

